The paper discusses the development of a bio-inspired algorithm, the Dendritic Cell Algorithm, which processes information at multiple levels of resolution. This algorithm falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves the creation of information granules of variable structure. The algorithm also has applications in systems and control (cs.SY) as it is used for detecting anomalous invading entities. Additionally, the paper discusses the parallels between the human immune system and artificial immune systems, which falls under the category of computational engineering (cs.CE) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
